<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,395,961]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,395,420]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is related to 
<taxonomicName box="[568,739,396,420]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multidentata">
<emphasis box="[568,582,397,420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[597,739,396,420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">multidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Shennonjia, Hubei, but clearly distinguishable from the latter by the epandrium and aedeagus (in 
<taxonomicName box="[620,790,432,456]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Stegana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="multidentata">
<emphasis box="[620,634,432,455]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[649,790,432,456]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">multidentata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: epandrium broadened on posterior margins, more wider than 
<number box="[206,219,468,492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[228,241,468,492]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="5.0">5</number>
high; aedeagus distinctly expanded submedially and with rhombic opening in ventral view).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="25" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,395,961]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[201,347,503,528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">Description.</emphasis>
Male terminalia: Epandrium roundly protruded ventrally, approximately twice as high as wide on posterior margins (
<figureCitation box="[365,432,540,564]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[419,432,540,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
). Cercus lacking pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[780,851,540,564]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[834,851,540,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Surstylus with 
<number box="[1043,1057,540,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="8.0">8</number>
prensisetae submedially (
<figureCitation box="[1352,1422,540,564]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[1405,1422,540,564]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
). Tenth sternite strongly protruded apicolaterally (
<figureCitation box="[695,764,575,599]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[748,764,575,599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="3.0">3</number>
</figureCitation>
). Paramere with ca. 
<number box="[996,1038,575,599]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6</number>
sensilla (
<figureCitation box="[1144,1246,575,599]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus with globular projections bearing finely serrated processes basally (
<figureCitation box="[864,968,612,636]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">Figs 4, 5</figureCitation>
); nearly oval on opening in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[159,229,647,671]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,229,647,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
). Gonopods round apically, not protruded dorsomedially (
<figureCitation box="[878,947,647,671]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 6" captionStartId="1.[151,263,1863,1886]" captionTargetBox="[256,1327,1037,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[234,1353,1023,1839]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 6. Stegana (Steganina) danbaensis sp. nov., male terminalia: 1. Epandrium (epan), cercus (cerc) and surstylus (sur) (lateral view); 2. surstylus (ventral view); 3. 10 th sternite (ventral view); 4, 5. hypandrium (hypd), parameres (pm), aedeagus (aed) and aedeagal apodeme (aed a) (ventral and lateral view); 6. gonopods (ventral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/215440/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="25">
Fig. 
<number box="[931,947,647,671]" pageId="1" pageNumber="25" value="6.0">6</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
